Jeux pour lire avec Sami et Julie, une application pour que votre enfant apprenne à lire avec la méthode syllabique tout en s’amusant !
À travers 4 jeux progressifs, votre enfant va d’abord reconnaître les sons, puis former des syllabes sur le mode « b » et « a », « ba ». Ensuite, il pourra compléter des mots et enfin, il formera des phrases.
Une application spécialement conçue pour que les enfants soient autonomes et s’amusent avant tout avec :
- toutes les consignes audio ;
- 2 personnages, Sami et Julie, qui encouragent l’enfant à chaque étape ;
- un environnement joyeux et ludique ;
- des exercices intuitifs et intelligents élaborés par des spécialistes.

Vancouver Trees is a mobile app that describes commonly cultivated deciduous and evergreen trees in the Metro Vancouver area. The app is available in a professional version (Vancouver Trees Pro), and in a no-frills basic version (Vancouver Trees Basic). Users of both apps can:

    · browse and search an extensive database of nearly 1,000 trees by common or scientific name, each one accurately described by its identification features, ecological needs and availability;
    · advanced search for trees based on a long list of identification features and landscape use criteria;
    · view essential information on each tree;
    · read detailed descriptions for each genus and species;
    · search a gallery of more than 2,500 tree images; and
    · view and search a glossary of more than 350 terms.


Users of Vancouver Trees Pro will also be able to:

    · share essential information on each tree;
    · view high-resolution and share low-resolution tree images from the gallery;
    · view over 3,500 mapped tree locations in the Metro Vancouver area;
    · create favourite plant lists, either to share or to make a personal archive for quick referencing; and
    · add notes on favourite lists to individually tagged plants.


The app is a comprehensive resource for landscape architects, students in landscape architecture, landscape professionals, gardeners, arborists, or anyone else with an interest in Vancouver’s trees. The app will help users to make informed decisions when planting and designing with trees. Proceeds from the sale of Vancouver Trees go to the UBC Botanical Garden.
